name: MarcoYoga Power Lunch
address: 25 West 31st Street Floor 6, New York, NY 10001
description: This class is an inward journey of Raja Yoga, the Royal Yoga, and consists of intelligent sequencing with attention to precision and alignment. All levels welcome.Mats and props provided.

name: Livestream Dharma Flow
description: In this class you will be guided to look inward as you move your body to your breath, and shift from thinking to feeling. You will be offered a focus based on yogic philosophy that aligns with the world we live in, as well as the sequence your body is moving through. Whether building to a synchronized, rhythmic flow or… working on a specific action, this all levels class focuses on creating clarity in the mind and grounding you into your body as we link the physical practice of yoga to our everyday lives. *Zoom link for class will be sent 10 minutes prior to class. The sign up window for every class closes 12 minutes prior to the start of class

name: Livestream: Bar Method Express
description: Low impact. High reward. Our classic interval-training workout is designed to help you lose inches by burning fat and sculpting lean muscles. A well-designed sequence of specific movements will target and reshape your muscles. And stretches incorporated throughout the class will tone and elongate your body. The best method to… transform and renew you.45 minutes  Who it's for:Everyone  especially those seeking optimal fat-burning workouts and full-body transformation.  What you can gain:Stronger, leaner musclesIncreased flexibilityImproved posture, core strength and balance

name: Hour L2 LIVESTREAM
address: 135 West 20th Street 6th Floor b/w 6th & 7th Ave, New York, NY 10011Midtown
description: This is a one hour version of our Level 2 class  a well-rounded practice in a shorter amount of time. You have an understanding of the basic poses and transitional movements of a Vinyasa class (down dog, plank, chaturanga, cobra/upward dog). Youll get more dynamic sequences with challenging poses, subtle… alignment of basic poses, and an introduction to other yoga practices.  THIS IS AN ONLINE CLASS! Sign up here, and you'll receive an email to the address associated with your Yogamaya account with a link to take your class from afar.  First time joining us online?  If you are using a computer/laptop, please visit www.zoom.us to sign up. If you are joining us on your mobile device (phone, iPad, tablet, etc.), please download the Zoom app.  Please take a few moments to get to know the Zoom software, as it may be difficult for us to troubleshoot once you are in the class. If you have questions, please e-mail info@yogamayanewyork.com.

name: VIRTUAL Clash Cardio
description: A perfect open level class for Afro & Soca Lovers looking for a good sweat! Beginners get familiar with basic sequencing through a simplified version of ILLYs Dance CLASH routines and avid movers/dancers are welcomed to build stamina and endurance. Class starts with a warm up which builds into the Dance CLASH routine… for the day. We follow up with a body weight burn out and close with a light stretch! Class is conducted with predominately Soca music but Afro music is occasionally thrown in the mix as well. Dance movement is inspired by Caribbean Soca, Traditional west African and Afro street styles.

name: VIRTUAL: Mom, Dad & Me!
description: (30 minute class) Mom, Dad & Me! Want to get your kids moving? Want to get them off of those devices! Join Kelly for a kids movement and fitness class that has some goodies for parents as well. (or notif youre actually trying to work!) Kelly regularly teaches kids classes, so let her lead your kids through some fun fitness that… will rejuvenate their little spirits and burn off some of that bottled up energy!

name: AERIAL SILK - LEVEL 1
description: Develop your strength, stamina and stability in Level 1 Silk. You should be able to perform a basic climb and create foot locks on both sides unassisted in the air. Class will begin with basic skills and conditioning, gradually progressing into learning more elaborate poses and tricks as well as longer sequences of aerial movement.

name: One Arm Handstand Training
address: 250 Front Street Ground Floor, New York, NY 10038
description: The one arm handstand is one of the most challenging movements out there, it asks for deep dedication and patience as well as a solid technical understanding of handstand. In this class we take students through the essential drills and alignment to put you on your path to the one arm handstand. To get the most out of… the class you should feel comfortable in freestanding handstand and be able to move your legs between different shapes. Class is available via Zoom link.

name: Little Heroes
description: Little Heroes (Ages 3 - 5) is an 8-stage certification program designed to enhance our students' developing mental and physical skills with a fun and motivational approach. Our curriculum consists of developing eight major skill requirements that are represented by eight different colors. These skills are essential for… participation in all areas of life, including school, home, sports, and other social settings:  FOCUS - This skill will help your child's concentration, listening, and reaction skills.TEAMWORK - Your child will learn to work and play alongside his/her peers. The more confident your child is while working with others, the more your child will develop character, better social skills, and leadership abilities.  CONTROL - Your child will learn about making the right decisions and know when to use/not to use their Taekwon-do skills.  BALANCE - He or she will develop good balance and better posture, which can improve other physical activities and reduce injuries.  MEMORY - We'll exercise your child's brain with mental activities to improve their thinking and memory for schoolwork.  DISCIPLINE - Your child will learn to take direction from teachers and elders, as well as take pride in doing the right thing at the right time.  FITNESS - Your child will learn about the importance of being healthy.  COORDINATION - We will help develop your child's coordination skills to improve reactions and decrease risks of injuries from physical activity.  With a different skill highlighted every week, you and your child can look forward to the following:  Improvement of motor skillsImprovement of listening skillsBetter study habitsConfidenceLeadershipResponsibilityPositive social interaction and working with othersAttention spanMotivation  Upon completion of the Little Heroes program, our students will receive an official certificate issued by Martial Arts Education Society. The Little Heroes program will also prepare our students for the Martial Mind Program and start their path towards their black belt in traditional Taekwon-do.

name: Martial Mind
description: Martial Mind (Ages 5 - 7) is an 18-24 month, traditional martial arts-based Social and Emotional Learning (SEL) certification program, inspired by Headmaster Kwok's program designed for formal education. We, as educators, aim to nurture the character development of our students so they can grow into respectful,… well-coping, and moral individuals. As children at this age are still in the early stages of developing cognitive skills, the belt system is divided into different checkpoints for the preparation of their entry to the Juniors program.Besides learning to kick and punch properly, as well as age-appropriate self-defense techniques, we will spotlight a key theme, such as respect, focus, integrity, and self-control. We will demonstrate the meaning behind the selected theme and how it benefits the students' social skills and emotional competencies through physical practice. We aim to guide students to transfer the skills learned in class to their lives in academic and home settings.  Upon completion of the Martial Mind program, our students will receive an official certificate issued by Martial Arts Education Society. They are expected to progress in our Juniors Taekwon-do program at an accelerated rate.

name: Semi-Private Supervised Play Session
description: Looking for a fun place to play for a couple of hours?Social bridge is just what it sounds like only better.These sessions are old-fashioned, home-style bridge, with a twist. There is someone there the whole time to help if you want it, to find you the right game, to even stop and give a few minutes talk on a particular area of the… game that your table wants to review or learn.Come with a friend, your own table, or come by yourself. Well always be able to find you a partner.These are semi-private in nature, meaning no more than one or two tables to an instructor. This is how they are different from our club Supervised Play Sessions which could be much larger. The session fee is $35.

name: Vinyasa | All Levels | Online, live via zoom
description: This is an online class that takes place live via Zoom. Sign up in advance of the class and receive an email invitation before the class begins. You'll need zoom account to join.  Vinyasa | All LevelsVinyasa is a moving meditation where each pose is strung together on the the thread of breath. At the Shala, vinyasa is shaped by the lineage… of Ashtanga Yoga: economic, rigorous, and challenging. All Level classes are a well-rounded blend of alignment and fluid movement. Open to beginning practitioners with some knowledge of foundational postures (Surya Namaskar, standing and seated poses, backbends), as well as intermediate and advanced practitioners interested moving in a gentler and more precise way. Guidance will be provided regarding safe alignment, strength-building, joint stabilization, and proper breathing technique.

name: LIVESTREAM: Advanced Flow
description: A dynamic, flowing class that integrates core strengthening sequences as well as options for arm balances and inversion sequences. This class is for students who feel completely comfortable in our Open level offerings and wanting to take their practice to a new level.Check out our Online Classes FAQ's page… for more info on registration.  https://www.bendandbloom.com/online-classes-faqs

name: Kids Boxing
description: The greatest gift we can give our kids is confidence to defend themselves physically, but also to score a goal, raise their hand, or speak their mind. Confidence is a skill that can be learned and boxing is the perfect teacher. How to stand, how to breathe, what to focus on and pushing past perceived limitations are just… some of the lessons that boxing has to offer...when taught correctly. We support out young boxers and encourage them to apply what they learn here, outside the ring as well. Our classes are non contact and are suited for all skill levels. Boxing is a perfect compliment as a second sport. Some of our current and former members play and excel at the collegiate and professional levels and attribute boxing to the their success.

name: FREE Family Yoga (Zoom)
description: FREE Kids and Family Yoga every Thursday on Zoom, with movement to build strength and gain flexibility as well as mindfulness and breath work built in to every session.  Heres how it works:  1.) You must be pre-registered 15 minutes prior to the start in order to access the Zoom live call.  2.) You will receive an email with the… private zoom link before the class starts.  3.) Click the link and youll be able to access the live zoom call at the time of the class (download/open zoom on your computer or phone).  About Niki  Niki Poveromo rediscovered her love of yoga when she became pregnant with her first daughter and started attending prenatal yoga classes regularly. The sense of community and the atmosphere in the studio made her keep coming back for more. Fast forward to 2017, two kids later, Niki completed her 200-Hour Yoga Teacher Training from that same studio, Yoga Vida, in NYC. She also studied Restorative Yoga with Abby Paloma and Ally Bogard at Yoga Vida.  Niki continued her training in the Fall of 2017, completing a 25-Hour Kids Yoga certification through Yogi Beans in NYC, and is currently working towards her 95-Hour Registered Childrens Yoga Teaching certification through ChildLight Yoga, already having completed training for Babies and Toddlers, Teens/Preteens, and Athletes.  Niki has also completed her Basics and Advanced Prenatal Yoga Teaching certification through ChildLightYoga, in November 2018 and May 2019 respectively. She loves that she can now offer a safe space and opportunity for community to moms-to-be that she was given when she was pregnant.  Niki was born and raised in Astoria, NY, but is now a Hoboken Lifer, with her hubby, two daughters and two pups.

name: Group Training
description: Ours are different from regular boxing classes you might find elsewhere in that you work with a group of trainers each time that you come in. All of our trainers are active or former professional athletes who are well-versed in what it takes to get you to achieve your goals in a challenging, exciting, yet safe way. They all… came from slightly different backgrounds and therefor you receive an excellent workout every time and there's always a little variety.  If you can make it in to the gym two or more times per week, choose the unlimited group training option. If you can't make it to the gym more than once a week, then the package of ten group lessons is the most cost effective option for you. You will join in the group lessons when you choose and you have three months in which to use them up.

name: LIVESTREAM YOGASPARK CLASS
description: Please join us for one of our brand new livestream classes, via Zoom. The same YogaSpark style in a whole new medium! The details: -Register for this class no later than 30 minutes before class start time-15 minutes prior to class, you will receive a link from one of our managers to a Zoom meeting, which you can access from… your desktop, laptop, iPad or phone. You will likely be prompted to download the Zoom app to whatever device you are using.-You will also receive a link to a Spotify playlist (see below).The class will open up to participants 15 minutes prior to class start time and will begin promptly at class start time. --We will sign you in to the class as you join the Zoom meeting.-You will have the option to be seen or not seen by your instructor. Should you choose to be seen, that will help them give you verbal adjustments and shout outs as well as create more of a class vibe, but it is entirely up to you! You will be muted once class starts but will be able to chat with the instructor if you have any questions.-Class will be an open level, challenging, fun power flow in the classic YogaSpark style, with plenty of modifications and options.-There will be no music during class, but your instructor will tell you when to press play on the Spotify playlist so that the class can move with the music in sync. You will likely need a second device to play the music from. Thank you for bearing with us during these technically challenging times, as we attempt to recreate the YogaSpark experience as best we can on various platforms!

name: Livestream Dharma Yoga 60 min
address: 121 Fulton Street 3rd Floor, New York, NY 10038
description: A gentle, yet powerful series of balancing, stretching, back bending, twisting and mild inverted postures follow. The physical posture practice (Asana) tones and invigorates the body and mind, leading to enhanced flexibility, strength, balance and concentration. Breathing exercises (pranayama) and meditative techniques… regulate the heartbeat, de-stress the nervous system and calm the mind. This practice ends with Deep Relaxation, breathing exercises and concentration/meditation to remove impurities and bring a sense of well-being to the body and radiant peace to the mind. Turn on your video for corrections from the teacher.

name: Evening Vinyasa Flow
description: In this all-levels class, you'll connect to your breath before you flow through a series of dynamic poses. Finish the week strong by building strength and flexibility with a flow that's always set to a chill new playlist. We'll end class with a short meditation to release heavy energy and walk into the weekend with a fresh, new intention.

name: Livestream Open Flow - Yoga
address: 100 Hudson Street  4th Fl. (entrance on 1st) , Hoboken, NJ 07030
description: Midday slump happens. Literally. Unplugd is the antidote... Sitting at your desk too long or typing away at the coffee shop? Thats when stress sneaks into the neck, shoulders, and upper back, your posture rounds, and breath becomes shallowoften leaving you exhausted by 3pm. Join US for a rejuvenating sesh that… realigns the spine, opens cramped hips, and mobilizes stiff joints. Carefully chosen poses will nourish your musculoskeletal body (bye bye social media neck) and increase blood flow to restore chilife force energy. And since healthy breathing is key for maintaining balanced energy, well incorporate breathwork to restore concentration and kick stress to the curb. Youll head back to work inspired and in the zone. Employee of the month anyone? OPEN LEVEL.

name: Virtual Mat Pilates
description: Come work out with Elevate from the comfort of your own home! This signature class will incorporate some of the same moves you love to do on the reformer (but on the mat) and more! Work your body in different ways strengthening and lengthening every inch! Abs, butt,arms and more finishing with a calming stretch!

description: A transformative class led by some of NYCs most experienced and dedicated teachers. Learn the art, science and language of yoga. All levels welcome.

description: Meridian Yoga combines traditional yoga asana with the body maps of Traditional Chinese Medicine for an exploration into yourself. This class can include pranayama, stretching and activating meridians, and self acupressure.Open / Intermediate Level

address: 61 4th Avenue 3rd Floor, New York, NY 10003Lower Manhattan
description: Come as You Are. A open-level and well-rounded practice thats appropriate for those with experience in group classes.

description: Dharma I | Beginner  This is the beginning level of the Dharma Yoga series. Students practice Surya Namaskar Vinyasa and Shiva Namaskar Vinyasa Level I to warm up the body, bring flexibility to all muscles and joints and wake up the nervous system. A beginner, yet powerful series of balancing, stretching, back bending,… twisting and mild inverted postures follow. description: Just like our regular Runners Strength class, this 45 minute class still focuses on full-body exercise but with an emphasis on upper body strength - chest, arms, core and back! Why? Well running isnt just about how strong your legs are. A lot of a runners power comes from the upper body and core. Coaches design 2-4 minute… blocks of intervals to help maximize performance. This class is open to all levels of fitness.  *Coaches may make use of resistance bands or weights, so have them on hand if you have them. No weights? No problem! All workouts can be modified with alternative equipment, household items or simply bodyweight. You can also purchase Coach Approved equipment here:https://milehighrunclub.com/coach-recommendations

Classes begin with a warm up focusing on postural alignment, followed by a combination of upper and lower body exercises using light weights, resistance bands, as well as weighted and unweighted balls. Afterward, we head to the mat for core work and close with an invigorating final stretch. In this intelligent barre class you will move from larger movements that get your heart pumping to "feel-the-burn" pulses and isometric holds, efficiently conditioning your body.

description: If you have never taken Aerial Silk and are new to aerial dance, this is the class for you. Your instructor will begin class by leading you through a series of strength, flexibility and conditioning exercises that will help prepare you later on transition into the air. You will learn basic climbing skills, as well as how to create locks… around your body using the fabric. After grasping these fundamentals, you will be prepared to join our beginner level Aerial Silk classes. We recommend that you take Intro to Silk 3-5 times or have instructor approval prior to joining Silk Level 1 classes.

name: HIIT STRENGTH AND MOBILITY  (Virtual CLASS)
address: THE HIIT CLUB 911 BERGEN AVE , JERSEY CITY, NJ 07306Journal Square
description: STRENGTH AND MOBILITY Muscular strength and endurance are key components to physical fitness. ... Muscular strength is defined as the ability of a muscle group to develop maximal contractile force against a resistance in a single contraction. Muscular endurance is the ability of a muscle group to exert… submaximal force for extended periods.Mobility: This refers to how freely a joint can move throughout its full range of motion. Muscle length (flexibility), muscle tension/ tissue quality and how the nervous system controls the joint all come into play. Mobility training can improve the range of motion of our joints and muscles. It can assist in improving our posture. Mobility training can alleviate 'everyday' aches and pains as well as improve our body awareness.Its important to be mobile at any age. The ageing process can take its toll on the body, so it is important that we stay mobile and supple to combat this. Benefits of Strength Training. Strength training is a great way to improve your physical performance, gain lean muscle and lose body fat. ... Bone density increases with resistance training, leading to stronger bones, and decreased risk of bone diseases such as osteoporosis, especially in the elderly.

Over the past decade, the genre has seen increased popularity across Latin American dance industry and now as well as acceptance within North American and European.

description: THE WELL Signature Support Circle provides an opportunity for you to develop more self-awareness and deepen your connections with those around you. Well gather to find answers to life's complex questions and practice living without judgment and in alignment with what we really need.

description: The practice of hatha yoga focuses on the total mastery of the physical body including all bodily functions and emphasizes and promotes spiritual and physical wellness, including disease elimination.Hatha yoga helps to balance the mind, body, and chakras (centers of energy) through specific asanas (postures) and… controlled, meditative breathing that complements the physical movements of the body.In yoga philosophy, hatha yoga was originally considered to be a preparation for spiritual yoga practice as control over the physical body is believed to assist in developing control over the mind and spirit.  Hatha is a Sanskrit word that can be broken down into two smaller words: ha, meaning sun, and tha, meaning moon... The word may also mean willful or forceful.  Yoga Nidra instills a sense of relaxation through deep rest and meditation.  Best For Beginners, or anyone who wishes to move a little more slowly in their practice for deep relaxation and gentle opening stretches.

After grasping these fundamentals, you will be prepared to join our beginner level Aerial Silk classes. We recommend that you take Intro to Silk 3-5 times or have instructor approval prior to joining Silk Level 1 classes.

name: Group Training
description: Ours are different from regular boxing classes you might find elsewhere in that you work with a group of trainers each time that you come in. All of our trainers are active or former professional athletes who are well-versed in what it takes to get you to achieve your goals in a challenging, exciting, yet safe way. They all… came from slightly different backgrounds and therefor you receive an excellent workout every time and there's always a little variety.  If you can make it in to the gym two or more times per week, choose the unlimited group training option. If you can't make it to the gym more than once a week, then the package of ten group lessons is the most cost effective option for you. You will join in the group lessons when you choose and you have three months in which to use them up.

name: Jam Sessions Music - Zoom Interactive Class
address: 123 W20th Street 2E Second floor, New York, NY 10011Midtown
description: IF THERE IS NO SIGN UP OR BOOK CLASS BUTTON THE CLASS IS FULL.  Jam Sessions via ZOOM are interactive! Unlike livestreaming, in these sessions your child's favorite teacher can see and interact with your child. Register for this class and receive a link and a password via email to log in and join the fun! Jam Sessions via ZOOM… will be limited to 8 participants. Join Kids at Work Teachers for 35 minutes of music from the comfort of your own home. Further instructions will be sent for participants that register at least 15 minutes before class! These sessions are $15 per class.  Before Class: Download zoom (https://zoom.us/download) well before class time. Please be aware that when joining this class there is the potential for participants to see one another. All audio will be muted except for teacher for MOST of the class. If you do not want to be seen simply disable your video.  Do I need anything for this class?Please gather any instruments you might have for our "Jam Session". Other objects such as pots and pans, wooden spoons, or Tupperware filled with beans or rice (reinforce with some tape) will work too! If you have bubbles or scarves/pieces of fabric please make them available as we may use those as well!  Didn't get the email with all the info to join the meeting? Check your spam! We'll usually send it about an hour before.

name: LIVESTREAM YOGASPARK CLASS
description: Please join us for one of our brand new livestream classes, via Zoom. The same YogaSpark style in a whole new medium! The details: -Register for this class no later than 30 minutes before class start time-15 minutes prior to class, you will receive a link from one of our managers to a Zoom meeting, which you can access from… your desktop, laptop, iPad or phone. You will likely be prompted to download the Zoom app to whatever device you are using.-You will also receive a link to a Spotify playlist (see below).The class will open up to participants 15 minutes prior to class start time and will begin promptly at class start time. --We will sign you in to the class as you join the Zoom meeting.-You will have the option to be seen or not seen by your instructor. Should you choose to be seen, that will help them give you verbal adjustments and shout outs as well as create more of a class vibe, but it is entirely up to you! You will be muted once class starts but will be able to chat with the instructor if you have any questions.-Class will be an open level, challenging, fun power flow in the classic YogaSpark style, with plenty of modifications and options.-There will be no music during class, but your instructor will tell you when to press play on the Spotify playlist so that the class can move with the music in sync. You will likely need a second device to play the music from. Thank you for bearing with us during these technically challenging times, as we attempt to recreate the YogaSpark experience as best we can on various platforms!

name: Livestream Dharma Flow
description: In this class you will be guided to look inward as you move your body to your breath, and shift from thinking to feeling. You will be offered a focus based on yogic philosophy that aligns with the world we live in, as well as the sequence your body is moving through. Whether building to a synchronized, rhythmic flow or… working on a specific action, this all levels class focuses on creating clarity in the mind and grounding you into your body as we link the physical practice of yoga to our everyday lives. *Zoom link for class will be sent 10 minutes prior to class. The sign up window for every class closes 12 minutes prior to the start of class

name: Virtual 15 Min. of Feet
address: 69 Columbia Street 3rd Floor, Brooklyn, NY 11201Columbia Street Waterfront District
description: Immediately following 30-minute movement on Friday is 15 minutes of feet! Take them together for the ultimate rejuvenation.15 minutes of foot ball work, foot strength, and foot flexibility. Working your feet has proven connection to loosening tension in the jaw and pelvic floor as well as helping ease back, hip, and… knee pain. Feet are amazing! Get to know what yours can do for you.  A Zoom link will be emailed to you from Dibs 10 minutes before class starts.  If your roommate or partner joins, we strongly suggest that they sign up as well so the instructor will be paid fairly and can teach effectively.

name: Hour L2 LIVESTREAM
address: 135 West 20th Street 6th Floor b/w 6th & 7th Ave, New York, NY 10011Midtown
description: This is a one hour version of our Level 2 class  a well-rounded practice in a shorter amount of time. You have an understanding of the basic poses and transitional movements of a Vinyasa class (down dog, plank, chaturanga, cobra/upward dog). Youll get more dynamic sequences with challenging poses, subtle… alignment of basic poses, and an introduction to other yoga practices.  THIS IS AN ONLINE CLASS! Sign up here, and you'll receive an email to the address associated with your Yogamaya account with a link to take your class from afar.  First time joining us online?  If you are using a computer/laptop, please visit www.zoom.us to sign up. If you are joining us on your mobile device (phone, iPad, tablet, etc.), please download the Zoom app.  Please take a few moments to get to know the Zoom software, as it may be difficult for us to troubleshoot once you are in the class. If you have questions, please e-mail info@yogamayanewyork.com.

name: Pilates Fundamentals - ONLINE
description: For those new to Pilates or experienced practitioners looking to refine their technique, this 60 minute class will flow through a Classic Beginner Sequence focused on the foundational and nuanced aspects of Classic exercises including Pelvic Tile, Isolation, Articulation, Lengthening, and Opposition.

name: LIVESTREAM BurnStrong CORE-FLOW
address: 46 West 46th Street 4th Floor Front, New York, NY 10036
description: ****ATTENTION******* Due to the coronavirus outbreak we are doing our best to protect the weaker members of our community (those with pre-exiting conditions, compromised immune systems, and the elderly) and practice social distancing we have switched to ONLINE CLASSES and THIS IS AN ONLINE CLASS.… Please do not come to our physical location in Midtown Manhattan, rather register for our online class via ZOOM and we can practice together (in spirit).  BurnStrong Core-Flow class description: YOGALATES. And we don't just mean "core yoga" we mean yoga + PILATES taught by a creative, well-informed yoga + PILATES teacher who cares about you and the health of your spine.  Stretch, and feel that Pilates-Burn in your core: BurnStrong CORE FLOW.  *All BurnStrong classes are done barefoot on mats.    https://zoom.us/j/6463292346

name: Online: GLOBAL SPOTLIGHT Open Feldenkrais
address: 126 East 13th Street, New York, NY 10003Lower Manhattan
description: The Feldenkrais Method, developed by Moshe Feldenkrais, is based on learning patterns of movement with the aim to develop and improve our awareness of the Quality of Moving. The practice of the method helps improve performance, as well as, avoid and cure injuries. While the Feldenkrais Method is designed for… all people, it is particularly beneficial for dancers who consciously deal and explore movement daily at a profound level.

name: Live Online: Level 1/Beginners
address: 150 West 22nd Street 2nd Floor, New York, NY 10011
description: Level I students, beginners as well as students who are brand new to Iyengar Yoga, will focus on fundamental postures including a basic inversion.

name: Semi-Private Supervised Play Session
description: Looking for a fun place to play for a couple of hours?Social bridge is just what it sounds like only better.These sessions are old-fashioned, home-style bridge, with a twist. There is someone there the whole time to help if you want it, to find you the right game, to even stop and give a few minutes talk on a particular area of the… game that your table wants to review or learn.Come with a friend, your own table, or come by yourself. Well always be able to find you a partner.These are semi-private in nature, meaning no more than one or two tables to an instructor. This is how they are different from our club Supervised Play Sessions which could be much larger. The session fee is $35.

name: Yoga Flow

address: 250 Front Street Ground Floor, New York, NY 10038
description: Core Yoga is a core conditioning class drawing from Yoga, Pilates, gymnastics/acrobatic conditioning as well as other fitness/movement styles. Class will offer full body mobility and strength work with an emphasis on proper breathing mechanics and core activation.

description: This class will be held online via Zoom.$10 drop in, free for all members with unlimited passes.You'll need a an account with Zoom (free), you might want to download the Zoom App. Register per usual via Mindbody or our free Namastuy App up to 30min before class & you'll get an email with a link and password to join in… 10min before class begin. This class is beneficial to every student, as it increases focus and relief from daily stressors. Accessible to all levels.

name: Livestream Dharma Yoga 60 min
address: 121 Fulton Street 3rd Floor, New York, NY 10038
description: A gentle, yet powerful series of balancing, stretching, back bending, twisting and mild inverted postures follow. The physical posture practice (Asana) tones and invigorates the body and mind, leading to enhanced flexibility, strength, balance and concentration. Breathing exercises (pranayama) and meditative techniques… regulate the heartbeat, de-stress the nervous system and calm the mind. This practice ends with Deep Relaxation, breathing exercises and concentration/meditation to remove impurities and bring a sense of well-being to the body and radiant peace to the mind. Turn on your video for corrections from the teacher.

name: be-ginner- GYROTONIC Tower Class
description: This class is our core group class and focuses on technique and proper alignment while doing Level 1 GYROTONIC exercises. We recommend it for everyone, regardless of level because it ensures a solid foundation in the principles of the GYROTONIC exercise methodology. You can expect hands-on assistance from the… instructor as well as a detailed explanation of how to do the movements.

name: Livestream Weekend Wine Down  - Yoga
address: 100 Hudson Street  4th Fl. (entrance on 1st) , Hoboken, NJ 07030
description: After a long week, what could be better than a deliciously relaxing yoga sesh followed by a tasty glass of vino? We think its the perfect pairing. So join US as we clear the mind, relax the body, and lift the spirit! To start, well get centered, then release excess, frenetic energy with gentle movement set to a soundscape of relaxing… vibes. Then well take it down a notch more, winding down with some grounding seated postures. Finally, well melt layers of deeply held tension, supported by bolsters, blankets, and blocks, in restorative postures that bring bliss to our urban souls! Before floating home, or wherever your weekend plans take you, youre invited to chill for a while longer, kicking back with the Urban Souls tribe and a complimentary glass of wine. Cheers! Heres to your health and happiness!

name: Hip hop I Ages (8-12)
description: Pre Hip-Hop is a class designed to teach the basics in different styles of Hip-Hop as well as some basic Break Dancing exercises, they can use in break dancing classes later on, as well as playing some fun games such as freeze dance to keep them moving, and having fun. They will be working on their performing abilities and high… energy to get ready for our event Dansanity Stars.

name: Original Hot Yoga 75 + Music Live Stream
description: Original Hot Yoga is a series of twenty-six Hatha Yoga postures and two Pranayama breathing techniques designed to provide a challenging, invigorating, rejuvenating and effective yoga experience. During this 75-minute class with music, you will work every muscle, tendon, ligament, joint and internal organ in… the entire body, giving you an incredible sense of well being.  This class is delivered by Zoom in partnership with FitGrid LIVE. You can enroll for this class up until two minutes before the scheduled start. You will receive an email from FitGrid LIVE starting an hour before the class with instructions.

name: Intermediate Level Reformer
description: Intermediate Level Reformer classes are ideal for clients who have consistently practiced and have a good understanding of the principles of Pilates as well as how to navigate the equipment. 55 minutes

name: ONLINE: Flow & Restore
address: 281 Greene Avenue 1st Floor, Brooklyn, NY 11238Clinton Hill
description: OPEN LEVEL  This well rounded class begins with guided movement to help you stretch, strengthen, breathe and connect. After working up a bit of a sweat the class will cool down with some meditative, restorative poses before heading into final Savasana.  Please make sure you sign up at least 30 minutes ahead of time. A link to… the online class will be sent to everyone in the roster 25 minutes prior to the beginning of the session. Email info@dou-yoga.com if you do not receive the link.

name: Restorative - ONLINE
description: In this gentle class you will truly learn what it is to relax. This class is practiced solely on the mat in restful and reclined positions. This unique restorative can be done in your home without the use of yoga props. It is the perfect way to relieve stress and connect with the self. No yoga experience required.

name: Row HIIT (Virtual Class) *ROWER REQUIRED
description: 30 Minute Virtual Class Using the Concept2 Rower at home follow us through 6 rounds of interval training . We use body weight exercises as well as some equipment like dumbbells and resistance bands.

name: Handstand Shapes & Movements (on ZOOM)
address: 250 Front Street Ground Floor, New York, NY 10038
description: So you can kind of hold a handstand. First, congrats, it's hard work. In this class we will work on explore the different shapes you can make while balancing on your hands. Class will begin with full body conditioning & flexibility drills to prepare your body for a handstand practice. Once our bodies are prepped we will… work through drills to play with new or familiar shapes, entrances and exits in the handstand as well as techniques for shape changing. Techniques will draw on handstands and conditioning from partner acrobatics, gymnastics, yoga, capoeira and break dancing. Class is available via ZOOM link that will be emailed to you before class begins.

name: Salsa Shines (Beg/Int Level)
address: 189 Brunswick Street, 3rd Fl, Jersey City, NJ 07302
description: Join us for an online session of social Latin Salsa with Dakota. We'll start with a warmup to get the blood flowing and go over some basic steps or stretches, then transition into a Salsa solo routine, also known as a "shine" that can be incorporated into your social dancing. Class will be held via Zoom and the link will be… emailed 15 minutes before class. You can use Zoom on your laptop via web browser or app, or download it on your phone. You'll be able to send in questions as well for Dakota to address. Work up a sweat, improve your dancing and connect with your dance community!

name: Sattva Sunset Flow in the Park
description: Join us as we gather once more for Open Level Flow classes safely distanced outdoors!  You will find us at this lovely spot at Riverview on the Ogden Ave. and Griffith Street. Classes are by REGISTRATION ONLY, open to Monthly members and available with Sattva class packages, singles can be purchased as well.… NO DROP INS, no sales transactions on site. We must limit class size for distancing purposes.  Please bring a mat and be prepared to distance 6 feet apart. All participants must wear a mask upon arrival to check in with the teacher, masks can be removed when the practice begins..    WEATHER PERMITTING, you will be contacted no less than 1 hour before class if cancelled.
